{
  "stem": "14060.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It became sort of scorched, but it was still intact, and the string, as well.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And then the domestic of the house went and fetched it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But somebody Jewish had to go with her, to make sure that nothing is tampered with the food 'til it gets home.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I must take you a few hours back.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "How was it on Shabbat morning?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "First of all, in the school-- I went to a non-Jewish school.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was Shabbat morning, we went to school like any other day. 8 o'clock in the morning, whatever week it was-- on Yom Kippur or Rosh Hashanah, we got exemptions.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But on ordinary Shabbat, there was no exemption whatsoever.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What happened was that, at 8 o'clock in the morning, our domestic took my case-- or before 8-- and walked with me to school and placed my school bag down in school.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were exempted, even in the most anti-Semitic times, from writing.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they normally organize it that there were no written exams even, so as not to disturb the class, presumably.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so, therefore, boys above bar mitzvah age certainly could not attend to-- to Shabbat services in the winter, because it was too early.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In the summer, it was all right, because we could start start [INAUDIBLE], say, at 6:30 in the morning so we were finished in time and had a quick breakfast.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Now-- but the normal community, those who didn't go to school, the-- the shul started at 7:30 in the morning.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "By 9:15, 9:30, it was finished.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We had breakfast.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And after breakfast, you learned or you went for a walk or whatever.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Usual lunchtime.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then, in the afternoon, the families used to get together in our garden or we went to them.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
